was an appropriate deadline.

You  want  to  give  an  engineer  an  opportunity,  you  want  to  give
free-thinkers and people who have great ideas an opportunity to do
something,  but  you  don’t  give  them  unlimited  time  and  unlimited
money, in terms of length of time. So, I withdrew at that time, say-
ing Tony, you missed your deadline.

Let  me  ask  this.  I  guess  currently,  you  testified,  to  answer  your
question,  that  in  2003,  the  duPont  operation  did  not  meet  the  re-
